.TH SINGINE-RUNTIME 1 "2026-03-13" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-runtime \- inspect runtime capabilities and execute wrapped commands
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine runtime
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B runtime
command reports local runtime capabilities and executes Singine or external
commands inside a structured JSON envelope that captures terminal context,
sourced environment, and execution results.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B inspect
Show shell, JVM, Racket, and Emacs runtime information.
.TP
.B exec \fICOMMAND ...\fR
Run a Singine subcommand inside a runtime envelope.
.TP
.B exec-external \fICOMMAND ...\fR
Run an external binary inside the same envelope without shell interpolation.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SINGINE_SESSION_TOKEN
If present, the token prefix is included in
.B exec-external
payloads.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine runtime inspect
singine runtime exec bridge sources --db /tmp/sqlite.db
singine runtime exec-external collibractl community list --output json
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1)
